Joe. Would you please triage the bug?

Created an attachment (id=26535)
sample file failing to be opened on my machine

This sounds serious, and is likely related to the 4.1 enhancements which we 
are making to the Test Log viewer.

Bianca -- can you please take a look at this.  It needs to be the case that we 
can still open new execution history files on an old workbench.  In the past, 
we have not had problems when adding new attributes to the model, so we need 
to figure out why this is causing problems, and what we can do to ensure that 
old model code can still read the new model files (while of course not being 
able to take advantage of any new model features.)
Joe. I think you mean 4.1i2 instead of 4.0i2

Please note that the same driver version is used to open the file, but only the
driver which created the file can open it and not the other one that have the
file copied over to workspace.

In Test model, the containment reference of verdictLists in TPFExecutionResult
should be *transient* so that it will NOT be persisted. verdictList containment
is actually *derived* meaning it's volatile (not contributing to the state of
the object), transient (not persisted with the object) and non-changeable. It
should only be set externally. Test model is fixed to reflect this character.
With this fix, no execution history should be generated with "verdictLists"
attribute contained in the resource. So execution history created with this new
test model should be compatible with any previous version of TPTP.

Eugene, I am afraid the particular execution history referenced here has to be
fixed in order to work with any older version of TPTP.  There are two ways to
fix it:
1) regenerate the execution history with a new build (from tomorrow) that
contains this fix.  Or, if this is not an option
2) fix the problematic execution history by opening it with winzip, and then
notepad, search for "verdictList" and remove any attributes contains that
references.

verified in tptp.runtime-TPTP-4.1.0-200510140100 and problem does not exist anymore.

close bug
